==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thermobarometer
<hw>Ther`mo*ba*rom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thermo-</ets> + <ets>barometer</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for determining altitudes by the
boiling point of water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A siphon barometer adapted to be used also as a
thermometer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermobattery</ent>⟦br⟧
